308
00:20:30,762 --> 00:20:32,161
There's still some for you.

309
00:20:32,331 --> 00:20:34,299
Didn't you see the note
that l put on them?

310
00:20:34,466 --> 00:20:36,058
What note?

311
00:20:38,136 --> 00:20:40,104
This note.

312
00:20:42,207 --> 00:20:45,574
-We must've missed it.
-lt's not funny.

313
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:48,178
l was up all night baking these
for the open house...

314
00:20:48,347 --> 00:20:49,871
...and now l have to go buy them.

315
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:53,176
l'm still mad at you for blowing me off
getting the tree last night.

316
00:20:53,352 --> 00:20:54,819
l had to do that all by myself.

317
00:20:54,987 --> 00:20:57,080
We'll make it up to you today,
won't we, guys?

318
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,247
-We will?
-l bend over backwards...

319
00:20:59,424 --> 00:21:03,485
...to make Christmas and everything
else for that matter nice for this family.

320
00:21:03,662 --> 00:21:05,926
And none of you seem to care.

321
00:21:06,098 --> 00:21:09,465
l don't think you appreciate how much
work goes into this time of year.

322
00:21:09,635 --> 00:21:12,160
You just take it for granted
that it will all get done.

323
00:21:12,337 --> 00:21:15,465
Haven't you even noticed
how far behind we are?

324
00:21:17,509 --> 00:21:22,310
Okay, look, all l'm asking for
is you guys to help me out a bit, okay?

325
00:21:22,481 --> 00:21:24,972
So Christmas can be nice.

326
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:27,748
Sure, honey, whatever you need.

327
00:21:27,919 --> 00:21:28,943
You're right, Mom.

328
00:21:29,988 --> 00:21:31,956
-Our bad.
-Thanks.

329
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:35,719
lf you'll get the Christmas card
address list and staff gift list together....

330
00:21:35,894 --> 00:21:36,918
Absolutely.

331
00:21:37,095 --> 00:21:39,996
And if you'll go get
some new Christmas lights...

332
00:21:40,165 --> 00:21:42,565
...and if you get the decorations
for the outside...

333
00:21:42,734 --> 00:21:44,861
...and the tree ornaments
out of the garage....

334
00:21:45,037 --> 00:21:48,939
-You got it.
-Then we'll decorate it like we used to.

335
00:21:49,107 --> 00:21:52,873
-You can count on us, hon.
-Good, because l need you guys.

336
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:54,910
Family hug.

337
00:21:56,448 --> 00:21:57,847
Okay.

338
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:02,177
Okay, l gotta go. l have things to do.

339
00:22:03,055 --> 00:22:04,249
-Bye, Mom.
-Bye.

340
00:22:04,423 --> 00:22:06,618
-See you, hon.
-Bye.

341
00:22:09,528 --> 00:22:11,155
Don't even think about it.

342
00:22:22,774 --> 00:22:26,403
<i>Market Place is unfair.</i>
<i>All we want is our fair share.</i>

343
00:22:26,578 --> 00:22:30,514
<i>Market Place is unfair.</i>
<i>All we want is our fair share.</i>

344
00:22:40,926 --> 00:22:43,622
l knew it would be busy,
but this is crazy.

345
00:22:44,262 --> 00:22:45,661
Yeah.

346
00:22:48,633 --> 00:22:52,091
How late did you guys stay up
decorating last night?

347
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:53,760
We haven't started.

348
00:22:53,939 --> 00:22:55,736
Oh, look,
some of the girls are here.

349
00:22:55,907 --> 00:22:57,704
Mom, can you watch the register?

350
00:22:57,876 --> 00:23:00,310
-Sure.
-Thanks.

351
00:23:00,479 --> 00:23:03,880
-Hi, girls.
-Hi.

352
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:05,645
So glad you could make it.

353
00:23:05,817 --> 00:23:09,446
l look forward to coming here
to escape from my brood for a while.

354
00:23:09,621 --> 00:23:11,179
Especially this time of year.

355
00:23:11,356 --> 00:23:14,484
-Oh, but you love Christmas, Debbie.
-Well, well, we all do.

356
00:23:14,659 --> 00:23:16,854
But l'm with her.
After the week l've had...

357
00:23:17,028 --> 00:23:19,588
...l am so ready for a break.

358
00:23:19,765 --> 00:23:21,323
Well, now you can relax.

359
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,024
This is beautiful. Whose is it?

360
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:26,436
lt's mine. l'm making blankets
for the boys to take to college.

361
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:29,335
That's right, they're seniors now.

362
00:23:29,508 --> 00:23:33,035
l'm so jealous. You'll finally have
your house to yourself.

363
00:23:33,712 --> 00:23:35,646
-Hi, ladies.
-Hi, Rosemary.

364
00:23:35,814 --> 00:23:38,578
-Hi.
-l just had to get away for a little while.

365
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:40,843
We've got a reporter out
on maternity leave...

366
00:23:41,019 --> 00:23:43,681
...and l'm running ragged
picking up the slack.

367
00:23:43,855 --> 00:23:47,586
So, Joy, you promised to show me how
to do that beautiful butterfly stitch...

368
00:23:47,759 --> 00:23:49,818
-...you were using the other day.
-lt's easy.

369
00:23:49,995 --> 00:23:53,021
That will add
a lot of flair to your work.

370
00:23:53,198 --> 00:23:54,597
l'm all for flair, honey.

371
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:57,564
That may be
the understatement of the year.

372
00:23:58,804 --> 00:24:00,362
That's the way we do it in Texas.

373
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:02,398
Hi, everyone.

374
00:24:03,241 --> 00:24:05,709
Wow, l thought l was tired.

375
00:24:06,511 --> 00:24:07,637
Thanks, Rosemary.

376
00:24:07,813 --> 00:24:09,872
l didn't mean for it
to come out that way.

377
00:24:10,048 --> 00:24:11,572
That's okay.

378
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:14,878
lt's hard when you have little ones,
but they do grow up eventually.

379
00:24:15,053 --> 00:24:17,214
How about husbands?
Do they grow up too?

380
00:24:17,389 --> 00:24:20,984
l'm serious. l swear Glen truly believes
that l am Santa Claus.

381
00:24:22,327 --> 00:24:25,888
-That's nice.
-Thanks. l'm making eight of them.

382
00:24:26,064 --> 00:24:28,464
Six down, two to go.
Christmas on a budget.

383
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:30,897
lt's hard to come up
with affordable gift ideas...

384
00:24:31,069 --> 00:24:33,936
...especially when you have
to do your husband's shopping too.

385
00:24:34,105 --> 00:24:37,097
Why do you do that?
Make him shop for himself.

386
00:24:37,275 --> 00:24:39,243
Believe me, l've tried.

387
00:24:39,778 --> 00:24:41,609
Maybe you just
need to try a new tactic.

388
00:24:41,780 --> 00:24:43,975
Sometimes you just have
to take a stand.

389
00:24:44,149 --> 00:24:46,743
Did you read my article
about the grocery store workers?

390
00:24:46,918 --> 00:24:49,011
You wrote an article on the strike?
l missed it.

391
00:24:49,187 --> 00:24:50,814
l'll e-mail you a copy of it.

392
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:53,685
Well, tactics or not,
Christmas still has to get done.

393
00:24:53,859 --> 00:24:55,224
True.

394
00:24:55,393 --> 00:24:57,020
l'm no Scrooge...

395
00:24:57,195 --> 00:25:00,528
...but how's anyone supposed to get
get all this holiday stuff done?

396
00:25:00,699 --> 00:25:03,327
lf l didn't have these stolen moments
with you guys...

397
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:05,163
...l'd think l might just crack.

398
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:07,532
Sometimes
it's just so overwhelming.

399
00:25:07,706 --> 00:25:10,436
-Yeah, it's not easy.
-l know. l hear you.

400
00:25:10,609 --> 00:25:13,737
Maybe you should all
just do a little less this year...

401
00:25:13,912 --> 00:25:16,506
...and don't expect so much.

402
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:20,310
But l want this Christmas
to be the best Christmas ever.

403
00:25:34,666 --> 00:25:35,792
Mark.

404
00:25:35,967 --> 00:25:37,696
Mark.

405
00:25:39,371 --> 00:25:42,033
-Mark!
-Hey, Mom.

406
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:43,902
Where are the decoration boxes?

407
00:25:48,179 --> 00:25:52,639
Sorry, Mom. l was super busy
after school today.

408
00:25:52,817 --> 00:25:55,581
l had to finish my thesis outline,
l started writing a song.

409
00:25:55,754 --> 00:25:58,882
l lost track of time. lt's super sick.
l think you're gonna love it.

410
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,025
l'll play it for you later
when l get home.

411
00:26:01,192 --> 00:26:04,161
No, we're doing the tree tonight
and the outside decorations.

412
00:26:04,329 --> 00:26:06,058
About that. l promised Brittany...

413
00:26:06,231 --> 00:26:08,222
...l would take her
to the new Bourne movie.

414
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,732
You also kind of promised me
that we'd do the tree.

415
00:26:10,902 --> 00:26:12,199
Can l do it later?

416
00:26:12,370 --> 00:26:14,133
Heads up.

417
00:26:14,306 --> 00:26:16,103
Are you two trying
to make me insane?

418
00:26:16,641 --> 00:26:19,041
Nope, just heading
to basketball practice.

419
00:26:19,210 --> 00:26:21,644
-Tonight?
-l gotta go, l'm gonna be late.

420
00:26:21,813 --> 00:26:22,837
Peace out.

421
00:26:23,014 --> 00:26:25,676
Coach wants us to learn the new D
for the L.A. tournament.

422
00:26:25,850 --> 00:26:28,080
The girls varsity team
had the court earlier.

423
00:26:28,253 --> 00:26:30,153
The tree kind of looks small, Mom.

424
00:26:30,322 --> 00:26:33,382
lf you'd been there, you could've
chosen whatever tree you wanted.

425
00:26:33,558 --> 00:26:35,458
Right. See you later.

426
00:26:35,627 --> 00:26:37,595
Wait, where's your father?

427
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:40,959
