for granted that it gets done.

471
00:30:21,553 --> 00:30:22,679
And it's not fair.

472
00:30:22,854 --> 00:30:27,348
Okay, but isn't this strike thing
taking it a little too far?

473
00:30:27,525 --> 00:30:31,017
How else am l to get your attention?
You should want to pitch in...

474
00:30:31,196 --> 00:30:33,790
...and stop making me
the nagging mom and wife.

475
00:30:33,965 --> 00:30:35,626
Can't we have another chance?

476
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:38,234
Sure. Right after
you meet my strike demands.

477
00:30:38,403 --> 00:30:41,895
-Which are?
-They're very simple.

478
00:30:42,073 --> 00:30:45,008
One, appreciate
all there is to do around here...

479
00:30:45,176 --> 00:30:46,643
...especially at Christmas time.

480
00:30:46,811 --> 00:30:50,042
Two, acknowledge that you each
need to do your fair share.

481
00:30:50,548 --> 00:30:56,646
And three, do it, on your own,
without any pestering. Just do it.

482
00:30:56,821 --> 00:30:57,913
Just do what?

483
00:30:58,456 --> 00:31:00,617
Just do Christmas this year.

484
00:31:00,792 --> 00:31:04,319
-Hon, we've all been busy.
-And we're sorry.

485
00:31:04,495 --> 00:31:05,519
Yeah.

486
00:31:05,697 --> 00:31:09,155
That's not enough, l'm afraid.
Actions speak louder than words.

487
00:31:09,334 --> 00:31:12,497
-What about my Christmas party?
-And my holiday department party?

488
00:31:12,904 --> 00:31:17,238
l'm sure when you actually put
some effort into it, you'll get it all done.

489
00:31:17,408 --> 00:31:19,376
You don't think we can do this,
do you?

490
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:21,375
l'm quite certain that you can.

491
00:31:21,546 --> 00:31:24,538
l wouldn't do this otherwise.
Excuse me.

492
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:26,684
Can't we start
after my football banquet?

493
00:31:26,851 --> 00:31:29,581
lt's the day after tomorrow.
What about my cookies?

494
00:31:29,754 --> 00:31:31,221
Sorry. l'm on strike.

495
00:31:32,690 --> 00:31:34,783
Don't worry,
we'll take care of the cookies.

496
00:31:34,959 --> 00:31:36,358
Have you ever made a cookie?

497
00:31:36,527 --> 00:31:40,930
No. Hey, hon, where's the recipe
for your special thumbprint cookies?

498
00:31:41,432 --> 00:31:42,797
l'm on strike.

499
00:31:46,304 --> 00:31:49,068
Don't worry, guys. This is just
one of your mother's moods.

500
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:51,674
Everything's gonna be fine.
Put in a little effort...

501
00:31:51,843 --> 00:31:53,276
...and it'll all blow over.

502
00:31:53,444 --> 00:31:56,413
Hopefully before my faculty party.

503
00:31:56,581 --> 00:31:58,071
Sure, Dad.

504
00:31:58,616 --> 00:32:01,881
-Should l go buy cookies tomorrow?
-No, you should have a little faith.

505
00:32:02,053 --> 00:32:04,180
We'll find the recipe,
we'll go to the store...

506
00:32:04,355 --> 00:32:07,153
...we'll get the ingredients.
l mean, how hard can it be?

507
00:32:22,874 --> 00:32:25,934
-Where did you find this recipe?
-l found it online.

508
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:28,476
Why are there five chef hats?

509
00:32:28,646 --> 00:32:32,013
Because it's the best recipe.

510
00:32:33,418 --> 00:32:35,443
lt says
''highest degree of difficulty.''

511
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:37,713
Okay, well, that doesn't matter.

512
00:32:40,358 --> 00:32:42,292
All right, what's first?

513
00:32:43,027 --> 00:32:45,723
Okay, it says we have
to preheat the oven to 350...

514
00:32:45,897 --> 00:32:48,161
...and line the baking sheet
with parchment paper.

515
00:32:48,967 --> 00:32:51,299
Parchment paper?
l didn't see that at the store.

516
00:32:52,036 --> 00:32:54,436
lt's probably to make sure
that cookies don't stick.

517
00:32:54,605 --> 00:32:57,665
Here we go, wax paper.
lt's the same thing. That's good.

518
00:32:57,842 --> 00:32:59,275
All right. Next.

519
00:32:59,944 --> 00:33:04,005
lt says we have to do the wet
ingredients and separate the eggs.

520
00:33:04,449 --> 00:33:06,679
Separate the eggs?
What does that mean?

521
00:33:07,118 --> 00:33:10,315
Separate means keep the ingredients
apart from the other ingredients.

522
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:12,820
Didn't you guys learn anything
at school?

523
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:16,552
lt says we're gonna need the whites
for one part and yolk for the other.

524
00:33:22,433 --> 00:33:23,627
Okay, then.

525
00:33:30,074 --> 00:33:32,599
-You've seen Mom do this?
-No.

526
00:33:39,117 --> 00:33:41,347
Just use your fingers. Don't worry.

527
00:33:42,987 --> 00:33:44,750
-Okay.
-All right, so get the....

528
00:33:44,922 --> 00:33:46,184
-This?
-Yeah, use the spoon.

529
00:33:46,357 --> 00:33:49,019
-Just get the yellow out of there.
-Yeah, yeah.

530
00:33:50,061 --> 00:33:52,495
Just take the yolk out.
Just scoop it.

531
00:33:53,731 --> 00:33:55,289
Okay.

532
00:33:55,466 --> 00:33:56,660
Mark, help him.

533
00:33:56,834 --> 00:34:00,031
Pick it up, you've just gotta scoop it,
it's right there. You got it!

534
00:34:00,204 --> 00:34:01,501
You got it! You got it!

535
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:06,943
Nicely done, all star. l thought
you were good with your hands.

536
00:34:07,111 --> 00:34:09,944
Footballs and basketballs, yes.
Eggs, not so much.

537
00:34:10,114 --> 00:34:12,446
Look, don't worry about it.
Ten-second rule.

538
00:34:19,757 --> 00:34:21,019
Just don't tell Mom.

539
00:34:23,861 --> 00:34:26,091
Okay. All right.

540
00:34:26,264 --> 00:34:27,731
Give me that.

541
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:33,333
You guys mix the wet ingredients,
the eggs and the butter...

542
00:34:33,504 --> 00:34:36,701
...and l'll take care of the dry,
the sugar, the salt and the flour.

543
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:40,772
Why are we using fake butter?

544
00:34:40,945 --> 00:34:42,913
Because it's healthier
than real butter.

545
00:34:45,683 --> 00:34:47,310
Let's go, boys. We can do this.

546
00:35:11,409 --> 00:35:14,810
All right, l'm ready to mix.

547
00:35:14,979 --> 00:35:18,039
-You know how to use that thing?
-Of course l know how to use it.

548
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:20,474
Plug it in.

549
00:35:23,554 --> 00:35:24,680
All right.

550
00:35:31,829 --> 00:35:33,820
l think there's a speed control, Dad.

551
00:35:42,773 --> 00:35:43,908
All right.

552
00:35:48,713 --> 00:35:51,739
Hey, l thought you were on strike.

553
00:35:52,383 --> 00:35:53,714
l am at home...

554
00:35:53,885 --> 00:35:56,649
...but l'm not on strike
against Christmas.

555
00:35:57,188 --> 00:36:00,351
-You think this'll actually work?
-lt has to.

556
00:36:00,525 --> 00:36:02,425
l've been thinking
that Keith and Ryan...

557
00:36:02,593 --> 00:36:05,790
...they just have had it too easy
for too long.

558
00:36:05,963 --> 00:36:09,262
lt's no wonder l get so stressed out
during the holidays.

559
00:36:09,433 --> 00:36:11,560
Why should all of this rest
on my shoulders?

560
00:36:11,736 --> 00:36:12,760
Absolutely.

561
00:36:12,937 --> 00:36:14,268
They should be pitching in...

562
00:36:14,438 --> 00:36:17,236
...not just assume that you're gonna
take care of everything.

563
00:36:17,408 --> 00:36:20,571
And l agree,
which is why l'm joining this strike.

564
00:36:21,078 --> 00:36:24,411
-Well, welcome aboard.
-Thank you.

565
00:36:25,049 --> 00:36:26,846
We just have to get their attention...

566
00:36:27,018 --> 00:36:30,044
...and then things will change
for the better. You'll see.

567
00:36:34,392 --> 00:36:36,792
l didn't say add all the flour at once.

568
00:36:36,961 --> 00:36:38,019
l'm not a mind reader.

569
00:36:38,196 --> 00:36:39,390
Who knew you'd spaz...

570
00:36:39,564 --> 00:36:42,465
...and turn the mixer on too high,
again, l might add?

571
00:36:43,167 --> 00:36:45,727
Your Mom is gonna be
home right after the shop closes...

572
00:36:45,903 --> 00:36:47,837
...and we still haven't
toasted our nuts.

573
00:36:48,406 --> 00:36:50,670
-Dad, don't ever say that again.
-You're so weird.

574
00:36:51,309 --> 00:36:54,369
To roll the cookies in
after we dip them in egg whites...

575
00:36:54,545 --> 00:36:55,569
...you smart asses.

576
00:36:55,746 --> 00:36:58,510
You got the wrong flour.
l don't know what gluten-free is.

577
00:36:58,683 --> 00:36:59,707
lt's healthier.

578
00:36:59,884 --> 00:37:01,977
We're not gonna make
cookies as good as Mom's.

579
00:37:02,153 --> 00:37:04,383
They're gonna be better. All right?

580
00:37:04,555 --> 00:37:06,819
You guys roll and dip,
l'll take care of the nuts.

581
00:37:06,991 --> 00:37:09,118
Then we get these suckers
in the oven.

582
00:37:10,895 --> 00:37:12,192
No.

583
00:37:12,697 --> 00:37:15,427
Mom's gonna be shocked
when she sees what we did.

584
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:17,693
Yes, she will.

585
00:37:27,545 --> 00:37:30,639
You two are looking
exceptionally perky today.

586
00:37:32,083 --> 00:37:34,881
Yes, and l've been meaning to tell you.
l'm on strike.

587
00:37:35,052 --> 00:37:36,952
Me too.

588
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:38,722
Strike?

589
00:37:39,257 --> 00:37:42,158
-What kind of strike?
-Christmas strike.

590
00:37:42,326 --> 00:37:44,988
l got tired of doing
all holiday preparations by myself...

591
00:37:45,162 --> 00:37:47,130
...with no support from my family.

592
00:37:47,298 --> 00:37:49,732
So l've left it all
to Stephen, Mark and Jeremy.

593
00:37:49,900 --> 00:37:52,960
The strike is the only way
l could think of to get their attention.

594
00:37:53,137 --> 00:37:54,365
lt's the same at my house.

595
00:37:54,538 --> 00:37:57,871
l thought maybe they would help
if they saw that no one's doing it.

596
00:37:58,042 --> 00:38:02,172
This sounds interesting.
lt's downright ball-- Courageous.

597
00:38:02,346 --> 00:38:06,282
Hey, l just came by for some of that
Alpaca Marled yarn you guys have.

598
00:38:06,450 --> 00:38:08,850
Came at a good time.
Joy and Sharon are on strike.

599
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:10,146
They are?

600
00:38:11,822 --> 00:38:13,449
So, what are your strike demands?

601
00:38:14,191 --> 00:38:17,285
Well, it's not all that different
from the grocery-store workers.

602
00:38:17,461 --> 00:38:18,587
lt's about fairness.

603
00:38:18,763 --> 00:38:21,823
Appreciate all there is to do,
especially at Christmas time...

604
00:38:21,999 --> 00:38:24,763
...acknowledge that
they need to help, and cooperate.

605
00:38:24,935 --> 00:38:27,335
Doing their part
in the true spirit of Christmas?

606
00:38:27,505 --> 00:38:28,836
Exactly.

607
00:38:29,006 --> 00:38:31,497
Family helping each other.
Amen to that.

608
00:38:31,676 --> 00:38:35,669
Pete must truly believe in Christmas
fairies, because he doesn't lift a finger.

609
00:38:35,846 --> 00:38:38,542
l'm lucky if l can get him
to haul the tree into the house.

610
00:38:38,716 --> 00:38:41,981
The kids are focused on what
they're putting on Christmas gift lists.

611
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:45,213
Everything you guys are talking about
needs to change in my house.

612
00:38:45,389 --> 00:38:47,254
Glen thinks because
l'm a stay-at-home...

613
00:38:47,425 --> 00:38:50,292
...l must have time
to do all the decorating and cooking...

614
00:38:50,461 --> 00:38:54,124
...as if raising two children and taking
care of a house weren't enough.

615
00:38:54,298 --> 00:38:55,629
-l hear you.
-Not to mention...

616
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:57,734
...taking the kids to see Santa Claus...

617
00:38:57,902 --> 00:39:00,803
...then you have to get their pictures
made with Santa Claus...

618
00:39:00,971 --> 00:39:04,031
...put them on cards, take those cards
and give them to people...

619
00:39:04,208 --> 00:39:07,234
...who don't even open those cards.
Who wants to do that?

620
00:39:08,546 --> 00:39:10,377
l think you ladies
have something here.

621
00:39:10,548 --> 00:39:12,516
Definitely do. Count me in.

622
00:39:13,050 --> 00:39:14,176
Do you think it'll work?

623
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:16,616
Because l've never been
much of a rabble-rouser.

624
00:39:16,787 --> 00:39:19,551
Sometimes you just need to
let them notice the injustice.

625
00:39:19,724 --> 00:39:20,816
Then things will change.

626
00:39:20,991 --> 00:39:23,391
-This is the time for action.
-l'm on strike too.

627
00:39:23,828 --> 00:39:27,229
Ladies, this is just the beginning.
Our lives are gonna change.

628
00:39:27,398 --> 00:39:31,061
We are gonna make Christmas
fun again, instead of a burden.

629
00:39:31,235 --> 00:39:33,669
For all women.
By the time our message gets out...

630
00:39:33,838 --> 00:39:36,204
...this whole town will be on strike
for Christmas.

631
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:38,433
Yeah, it will.

632
00:39:44,882 --> 00:39:47,248
Dad. Dad.

633
00:39:48,219 --> 00:39:49,516
Dad!

634
00:39:49,687 --> 00:39:50,881
What the...?

635
00:39:51,756 --> 00:39:54,850
-What did you guys do?
-The fire extinguisher's in the closet.

636
00:40:00,464 --> 00:40:02,796
We need to open the door
and get rid of this smoke.

637
00:40:02,967 --> 00:40:05,026
Dad, l think that wax paper
was a bad idea.

638
00:40:05,202 --> 00:40:07,193
-And l think--
-Hey!

639
00:40:08,739 --> 00:40:11,173
lf you two want to live
to see your next birthdays...

640
00:40:11,342 --> 00:40:14,607
...you'll get another cookie sheet,
and start baking another batch now!

641
00:40:14,779 --> 00:40:16,110
Okay.

642
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,406
Whatever you say, Dad.

643
00:40:32,797 --> 00:40:34,230
They don't look bad, actually.

644
00:40:34,398 --> 00:40:36,593
We haven't even added
the jam to the thumbprint.

645
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:38,632
Well, let's try one first.

646
00:40:39,470 --> 00:40:41,267
Careful, they're hot.

647
00:40:51,749 --> 00:40:53,979
Jeremy, stop,
you're splashing water everywhere.

648
00:40:54,151 --> 00:40:56,449
Dad, those cookies are foul.

649
00:40:56,821 --> 00:40:59,654
l don't know what happened,
l thought it would be so easy.

650
00:40:59,824 --> 00:41:01,052
Clearly we need a plan B.

651
00:41:01,559 --> 00:41:03,117
Yeah?

652
00:41:03,294 --> 00:41:06,092
And we've got 20 minutes to get
this kitchen cleaned up.

653
00:41:06,263 --> 00:41:08,493
This is Mom,
she's on her way home.

654
00:41:08,666 --> 00:41:09,997
Hey.

655
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:11,992
l've got an idea.

656
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:02,683
-Hey, no snooping.
-Was the shop busy today, Mom?

657
00:42:02,853 --> 00:42:04,787
How's Gramms?

658
00:42:05,456 --> 00:42:07,890
Yeah, it was busy,
and since when do you two ask...

659
00:42:08,058 --> 00:42:09,548
...about the shop and Grandma?

660
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:11,786
-Just interested, l guess.
-Yeah.

661
00:42:12,796 --> 00:42:14,821
Why is your hair wet?

662
00:42:15,366 --> 00:42:19,063
Well, we finished with the cookies and
we went out back and shot some hoops.

663
00:42:20,905 --> 00:42:22,532
What happened
to your hand, honey?

664
00:42:22,706 --> 00:42:25,300
Oh, Mark, he hacked me
when l was driving down the lane.

665
00:42:26,310 --> 00:42:29,370
l don't know what that means
but it sure smells good in here.

666
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:31,845
How did the baking go?
l'd love to try a cookie.

667
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:34,210
No previews.

668
00:42:34,385 --> 00:42:38,446
You're gonna have to wait to try them
at the banquet just like everyone else.

669
00:42:40,457 --> 00:42:41,924
All right.

670
00:42:43,527 --> 00:42:45,017
Wait, are you still on strike?

671
00:42:45,195 --> 00:42:46,560
We made the cookies.

672
00:42:51,869 --> 00:42:53,530
Nice start.

673
00:42:58,842 --> 00:43:01,743
-She's not budging, Dad.
-Who's gonna help me with my party?

674
00:43:01,912 --> 00:43:04,176
-Gift shopping? The Christmas cards?
-Decorations?

675
00:43:04,348 --> 00:43:08,546
Guys, we just have to get through
the football banquet...

676
00:43:10,454 --> 00:43:13,190
...and then we're
gonna negotiate a truce.

677
00:43:17,027 --> 00:43:19,518
So when do you think
they'll get to the decorations?

678
00:43:19,697 --> 00:43:22,165
l hope soon.

679
00:43:22,333 --> 00:43:24,665
-l always like it when they're up.
-Yeah.

680
00:43:24,835 --> 00:43:28,965
Well, l for one am relishing the fact
that l don't have so much to do.

681
00:43:29,139 --> 00:43:32,267
-l'm loving this strike so far.
-Me too.

682
00:43:35,479 --> 00:43:38,414
Oh, what's Rosemary doing here?

683
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:43,877
She's here to interview me. She wants
to do an article about the strike.

684
00:43:44,054 --> 00:43:46,215
-Hey, you guys.
-Hi.

685
00:43:46,390 --> 00:43:48,620
-l'm just gonna grab my stuff.
-Okay.

686
00:43:48,792 --> 00:43:50,487
This is a good idea.

687
00:43:50,661 --> 00:43:53,221
l pitched it to my boss
as a great human-interest story.

688
00:43:53,397 --> 00:43:56,161
lt'll be good for the women in town
to see what we're doing.

689
00:43:56,333 --> 00:43:59,791
And you can mention my support
for the strike in your article.

690
00:44:00,237 --> 00:44:03,900
Thank you. l'm gonna get quotes
from Debbie and Laura too.

691
00:44:04,308 --> 00:44:06,833
This strike's about to catch fire.

692
00:44:15,753 --> 00:44:17,414
Should be heading out shortly.

693
00:44:31,068 --> 00:44:32,296
So football's done...

694
00:44:32,469 --> 00:44:36,337
...Ryan's already obsessing
about basketball season.

695
00:44:36,507 --> 00:44:39,237
Yeah, Jeremy said he and Ryan
were going to light it up.

696
00:44:40,010 --> 00:44:41,671
So how do you like the cookies?

697
00:44:41,845 --> 00:44:43,779
These are actually delicious.

698
00:44:43,947 --> 00:44:46,507
Yeah, you might not think so
after you hear this.

699
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:48,447
l've been trying to get you all night.

700
00:44:48,619 --> 00:44:51,383
l overheard Keith and Ryan talking
before we left.

701
00:44:51,555 --> 00:44:53,113
Jeremy found your secret recipe.

702
00:44:54,692 --> 00:44:57,160
That's all right.
l wasn't really hiding it from them.

703
00:44:57,327 --> 00:45:00,558
No, no, he found it
and they gave it to Hansen's Bakery.

704
00:45:00,731 --> 00:45:02,562
-That's who made the cookies.
-Hey, Mom.

705
00:45:02,733 --> 00:45:04,428
-Yeah?
-We've got to get going.

706
00:45:05,169 --> 00:45:08,138
Last day of school tomorrow.
l've got a Spanish final.

707
00:45:08,305 --> 00:45:10,865
-Okay, Joy, we'll talk.
-Good luck with that.

708
00:45:11,975 --> 00:45:13,533
-Good night, guys.
-Good night.

709
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:19,781
So did you like the cookies, hon?

710
00:45:19,950 --> 00:45:23,716
Actually, l did. They're amazing.
You guys did a fantastic job.

711
00:45:23,887 --> 00:45:26,913
-l knew you could do it.
-Well.

712
00:45:27,091 --> 00:45:29,150
Yeah. So you found my recipe?

713
00:45:29,326 --> 00:45:30,793
l remembered where you kept it.

714
00:45:30,961 --> 00:45:32,826
And the recipe was followed exactly.

715
00:45:32,996 --> 00:45:35,464
You see what we can do
when we put our minds together?

716
00:45:35,632 --> 00:45:38,294
We're pitching in and trying to meet
your strike demands.

717
00:45:38,669 --> 00:45:39,727
l see that.

718
00:45:46,777 --> 00:45:50,372
Hey! Coats in the coat closet,
or in your room.

719
00:45:50,547 --> 00:45:52,606
l'm just gonna put it
right back on tomorrow.

720
00:45:52,783 --> 00:45:53,841
Jeremy....

721
00:45:55,052 --> 00:45:56,314
Remember....

722
00:46:04,228 --> 00:46:06,822
-l'll be up in a bit.
-Okay, hon.

723
00:46:14,738 --> 00:46:18,003
Hello, Rosemary? Hi, it's Joy.
l'm sorry to call you so late.

724
00:46:18,175 --> 00:46:20,109
l was just wondering...

725
00:46:20,277 --> 00:46:24,077
...if there was time to add something
to that article for tomorrow.

726
00:46:24,748 --> 00:46:26,147
Good.

727
00:46:31,989 --> 00:46:34,617
Have you guys seen the newspaper
today? lt's not outside.

728
00:46:35,325 --> 00:46:36,724
Jeremy must've grabbed it.

729
00:46:38,262 --> 00:46:40,287
Hey, so, hon...

730
00:46:40,998 --> 00:46:43,626
...since we made a good-faith gesture
with the cookies...

731
00:46:43,801 --> 00:46:47,134
...l was thinking
that maybe we could...

732
00:46:47,304 --> 00:46:50,330
...you know,
negotiate a truce to this strike?

733
00:46:50,507 --> 00:46:54,068
Yeah, Mom, we're really sorry
and this cereal sucks.

734
00:46:54,244 --> 00:46:56,474
-We worked hard on those cookies.
-You must've.

735
00:46:56,647 --> 00:46:58,672
They certainly were delicious.

736
00:47:00,250 --> 00:47:01,478
Have you guys seen this?

737
00:47:02,119 --> 00:47:03,484
How could we? You took it.

738
00:47:06,089 --> 00:47:08,216
Anything interesting
in the news today?

739
00:47:08,392 --> 00:47:11,327
l haven't finished it yet,
but it's all about us.

740
00:47:11,695 --> 00:47:14,323
Everything in that article
is the truth...

741
00:47:14,498 --> 00:47:17,194
...including your little cookie scam.

742
00:47:17,835 --> 00:47:18,893
How'd you find out?

743
00:47:19,069 --> 00:47:21,560
l know all, and see all.

744
00:47:21,738 --> 00:47:23,228
You're one scary dude, Mom.

745
00:47:23,707 --> 00:47:25,572
So did you even make any cookies?

746
00:47:25,742 --> 00:47:26,970
-Yeah. You kidding?
-Yeah.

747
00:47:27,144 --> 00:47:30,272
They just tasted
more like biological weapons.

748
00:47:30,447 --> 00:47:33,007
Will you call off the strike now,
please?

749
00:47:33,183 --> 00:47:35,811
Remember my strike demands?

750
00:47:36,220 --> 00:47:38,211
Yeah, they're in the article,
in bold print.

751
00:47:38,388 --> 00:47:41,516
Yeah, well, taking a family recipe...

752
00:47:41,692 --> 00:47:44,786
...and giving it to a bakery
to make the cookies for you...

753
00:47:44,962 --> 00:47:47,726
...isn't exactly in the spirit
of meeting those demands.

754
00:47:47,898 --> 00:47:50,196
You know, l was so proud
when l thought...

755
00:47:50,367 --> 00:47:52,198
...you had actually made
those cookies.

756
00:47:52,369 --> 00:47:55,429
Now, l know you were just trying
to dupe me into ending the strike.

757
00:47:55,606 --> 00:47:58,234
-Have you actually read this article?
-Of course l have.

758
00:47:58,408 --> 00:48:00,808
''My husband and sons need
to learn that Christmas...

759
00:48:00,978 --> 00:48:03,003
...doesn't just magically appear...

760
00:48:03,180 --> 00:48:05,705
...and their selfish ways
need to change.''

761
00:48:05,883 --> 00:48:08,875
-You said that?
-That's a little out of context.

762
00:48:09,052 --> 00:48:10,952
That article makes
us look bad, Mom.

763
00:48:11,121 --> 00:48:14,181
And you told them about the cookies?
She makes us look like idiots.

764
00:48:14,524 --> 00:48:16,651
And that's my fault how exactly?

765
00:48:17,060 --> 00:48:20,791
ln case you forgot,
you betrayed me.

766
00:48:20,964 --> 00:48:22,363
And now the whole town knows.

767
00:48:22,532 --> 00:48:25,433
And l see you gave them
a great picture to go with the article.

768
00:48:25,602 --> 00:48:27,263
You're very handsome
in that picture.

769
00:48:27,437 --> 00:48:31,168
Honey, the way she wrote this article,
we're marked men now.

770
00:48:31,341 --> 00:48:33,866
And you should be
after what you did.

771
00:48:35,312 --> 00:48:37,405
Hey, you ready to head to work?

772
00:48:37,581 --> 00:48:40,277
Or are you busy displaying
the arrogance and laziness...

773
00:48:40,450 --> 00:48:42,475
...of a man who doesn't appreciate
his wife?

774
00:48:42,653 --> 00:48:44,450
You're quite the role model,
Stephen.

775
00:48:46,323 --> 00:48:50,020
-Those weren't my exact words, Keith.
-l've had calls from other professors.

776
00:48:50,193 --> 00:48:52,821
l think you're in for quite a bit
of razzing today.

777
00:48:52,996 --> 00:48:55,294
Why are you spared?
lsn't your wife on strike too?

778
00:48:55,465 --> 00:48:57,626
Yes, and l'm not happy about it.

779
00:48:57,801 --> 00:48:59,530
But the article isn't about me.

780
00:48:59,903 --> 00:49:03,464
You know, this isn't what l wanted.
My strike demands are right here.

781
00:49:03,640 --> 00:49:05,608
They're simple.

782
00:49:06,009 --> 00:49:09,877
Well, it may not be what you wanted,
but it's what you got.

783
00:49:19,356 --> 00:49:22,120
So l'm guessing
you're not calling off the strike.

784
00:49:24,227 --> 00:49:26,991
That's the loser from the article.
What a jerk.

785
00:49:27,164 --> 00:49:28,426
Yeah.

786
00:49:30,167 --> 00:49:32,192
-Are you going now?
-Yeah.

787
00:49:32,369 --> 00:49:33,734
Okay, l'll bring the book.

788
00:49:33,904 --> 00:49:37,101
-Yeah, nice article.
-How can he show his face?

789
00:49:50,487 --> 00:49:52,853
-Hey.
-Hey.

790
00:49:53,023 --> 00:49:55,014
Rosemary's article was great.

791
00:49:55,192 --> 00:49:58,093
l loved her clever use
of ''Cookiegate.''

792
00:49:58,261 --> 00:50:01,628
So underhanded by the guys,
and a prize recipe too.

793
00:50:01,798 --> 00:50:04,665
-What are you doing here early?
-l wanted to get some stuff...

794
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:06,826
...before my day got crazy.
What's going on?

795
00:50:07,004 --> 00:50:09,438
-l don't know. But let's go see.
-l'll grab the door.

796
00:50:16,213 --> 00:50:18,704
Mom, what is going on?

797
00:50:18,882 --> 00:50:21,043
Seems your strike demands...

798
00:50:21,218 --> 00:50:24,119
...have touched a chord in the women
in this town.

799
00:50:25,589 --> 00:50:28,285
The Christmas strike has generated
quite a bit of interest.

800
00:50:28,458 --> 00:50:30,858
l'm sure your article
had something to do with that.

801
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:32,791
l realized after l read the article...

802
00:50:32,963 --> 00:50:35,932
...that the only way to truly make
a difference is with numbers.

803
00:50:36,099 --> 00:50:38,829
l need to teach my husband
a lesson before it's too late...

804
00:50:39,002 --> 00:50:42,529
...and before he infects the kids
with that lazy-ass attitude of his.

805
00:50:42,706 --> 00:50:45,573
And in order to do that,
we need to unite.

806
00:50:45,742 --> 00:50:47,801
She posted a link
to Rosemary's article online.

807
00:50:47,978 --> 00:50:51,038
l did too and we created a page for it.
This strike is going viral.

808
00:50:51,214 --> 00:50:54,183
You mean you are now organizing
the Christmas strike, Laura?

809
00:50:54,351 --> 00:50:56,251
There's a little activist
in me after all.

810
00:50:56,420 --> 00:50:59,184
Look at these comments
of support from women all over town.

811
00:50:59,356 --> 00:51:03,952
''l'm with you 1 00 percent.
lt's about time we took a stand.

812
00:51:04,127 --> 00:51:06,095
Way to go, girls.''

813
00:51:06,263 --> 00:51:09,562
lt looks the whole community
is behind your cause now, Joy.

814
00:51:09,733 --> 00:51:11,098
Right, girls?

815
00:51:11,268 --> 00:51:14,237
We're tired of being undervalued
and underappreciated. Right?

816
00:51:14,404 --> 00:51:17,168
We're boycotting until our families
cooperate and pitch in.

817
00:51:17,340 --> 00:51:18,364
Right.

818
00:51:18,542 --> 00:51:20,510
So do you have any comment, Joy?

819
00:51:20,677 --> 00:51:23,737
Yes. Yes, l do. lt really means a lot
that you all are here.

820
00:51:23,914 --> 00:51:26,712
l realize that this strike
isn't just about me.

821
00:51:26,883 --> 00:51:28,475
lt's about all of us.

822
00:51:28,652 --> 00:51:30,449
And now that we are united...

823
00:51:30,620 --> 00:51:33,418
...the days of women
making the holidays happen alone...

824
00:51:33,590 --> 00:51:35,854
...will soon be over
and this strike will succeed.

825
00:51:36,026 --> 00:51:40,122
So in the words of Gloria Steinem
or somebody:

826
00:51:40,297 --> 00:51:43,198
''Solidarity now
and solidarity forever.''

827
00:51:43,366 --> 00:51:46,096
-Yeah. Strike.
-Strike. Strike. Strike.

828
00:51:53,143 --> 00:51:54,201
We're so screwed, Dad.

829
00:51:55,745 --> 00:51:57,645
This is gonna be
the worst Christmas ever.

830
00:51:57,814 --> 00:51:59,475
You hear about the rally yesterday?

831
00:51:59,649 --> 00:52:01,480
Mom's got the whole town
behind her now.

832
00:52:01,651 --> 00:52:04,552
-That's a lot of estrogen.
-Jeremy, l get it.

833
00:52:04,721 --> 00:52:06,416
l also get that my holiday party...

834
00:52:06,590 --> 00:52:08,717
...happens to be taking place
in this house...

835
00:52:08,892 --> 00:52:11,258
...in two days
and l have nothing prepared for it.

836
00:52:11,428 --> 00:52:14,192
Not to mention that we have
also done absolutely nothing...

837
00:52:14,364 --> 00:52:17,765
...for Christmas. So yes,
right now, we're screwed.

838
00:52:18,802 --> 00:52:21,066
-You seem stressed.
-You think?

839
00:52:21,238 --> 00:52:22,262
Don't you have school?

840
00:52:22,439 --> 00:52:24,100
We're out for winter break,
remember?

841
00:52:24,274 --> 00:52:27,266
Well, good, because we need
to start getting ready for Christmas.

842
00:52:27,444 --> 00:52:31,210
l thought your Mom was gonna cave,
but that's not gonna happen now.

843
00:52:31,381 --> 00:52:33,975
Maybe that's
because she has a point.

844
00:52:36,953 --> 00:52:39,319
Yes, she's got a point.

845
00:52:39,489 --> 00:52:42,185
The holidays are a full-time job
that she made look easy...

846
00:52:42,359 --> 00:52:43,986
...even when it wasn't. l get it.

847
00:52:44,161 --> 00:52:46,925
She's thrown down the gauntlet
with this newspaper article.

848
00:52:47,097 --> 00:52:48,758
This is war now.

849
00:52:49,533 --> 00:52:51,524
But we can do this.

850
00:52:51,701 --> 00:52:53,532
Here's the list.

851
00:52:54,337 --> 00:52:55,964
-That's a lot of stuff.
-Yes, it is.

852
00:52:56,139 --> 00:52:58,198
We need to get started.
Where's your brother?

853
00:52:58,375 --> 00:53:00,605
Went to beg Brittany
to help him with the party.

854
00:53:00,777 --> 00:53:01,971
We need the tree up...

855
00:53:02,145 --> 00:53:04,113
...and the house decorated
before my party.

856
00:53:04,281 --> 00:53:07,182
We need to find a caterer fast.
We need to go gift shopping.

857
00:53:07,350 --> 00:53:08,544
This close to Christmas?

858
00:53:12,889 --> 00:53:14,288
This place is a nightmare.

859
00:53:14,457 --> 00:53:16,084
The women sneering and yelling.

860
00:53:16,259 --> 00:53:17,749
-Jackass.
-And the guys?

861
00:53:17,928 --> 00:53:20,260
All pissed. l thought that guy Ted
was your friend.

862
00:53:20,430 --> 00:53:22,694
-Santa told you to go--
-l heard what Santa said.

863
00:53:22,866 --> 00:53:24,128
Let's go to the car.

864
00:53:24,301 --> 00:53:26,428
l knew that picture of us
was gonna be trouble.

865
00:53:26,603 --> 00:53:30,004
lt's all over the lnternet. Someone
posted a video from Mom's shop.

866
00:53:30,173 --> 00:53:32,334
Now we'll have to find
somewhere else to shop.

867
00:53:32,509 --> 00:53:35,842
Hey, Keith, don't go in there.
lt's not safe.

868
00:53:36,012 --> 00:53:38,480
l have to, thanks to you.

869
00:53:38,915 --> 00:53:41,748
-lsn't that Mom's friend, the reporter?
-Yes, it is.

870
00:53:41,918 --> 00:53:44,011
Mr. Robertson?

871
00:53:45,155 --> 00:53:48,283
Hi. Rosemary Channing,
Joy's friend from the <i>Herald.</i>

872
00:53:48,458 --> 00:53:49,857
l know who you are, Rosemary.

873
00:53:50,026 --> 00:53:52,256
That's quite the hatchet job
you did on us.

874
00:53:52,429 --> 00:53:56,024
l'd like to interview you to get the male
perspective on the Christmas strike.

875
00:53:56,199 --> 00:53:59,657
l'm here talking to other men
but l'd really like to talk to you.

876
00:53:59,836 --> 00:54:02,100
How can l trust
you're gonna be objective?

877
00:54:02,706 --> 00:54:04,173
Mr. Robertson, l'm a journalist.

878
00:54:04,341 --> 00:54:07,799
l don't let my personal viewpoints
interfere with my work.

879
00:54:09,145 --> 00:54:11,136
-Okay, l'll do it.
-You will?

880
00:54:11,314 --> 00:54:13,248
Yeah. Meet us at our house at 4:00.

881
00:54:13,416 --> 00:54:16,852
Great. Great, l'll see you then.
Thank you.

882
00:54:17,020 --> 00:54:18,487
Sure you know what you're doing?

883
00:54:18,655 --> 00:54:21,624
Call your brother and tell him
to meet us at the house.

884
00:54:21,791 --> 00:54:24,316
We're gonna get our side
of the story out there.

885
00:54:24,494 --> 00:54:26,962
lt's time to turn the tide
on this strike.

886
00:55:05,068 --> 00:55:07,730
-Looks all right, Dad.
-Thanks, Mark.

887
00:55:07,904 --> 00:55:09,872
Where's Mom's angel ornament...

888
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:12,702
...and the ornaments we made with her
when we were little?

889
00:55:12,876 --> 00:55:16,642
Well, l couldn't find space for it,
so l went for a simpler theme.

890
00:55:16,813 --> 00:55:19,839
-Did you find that gift-buying website?
-Mission accomplished.

891
00:55:20,016 --> 00:55:21,347
Take care of Christmas cards?

892
00:55:21,518 --> 00:55:24,681
l downloaded the e-mails from the list
and l sent them e-cards.

893
00:55:24,854 --> 00:55:26,788
Good. What did it say?
l'm sure it's fine.

894
00:55:26,956 --> 00:55:29,618
Get this place cleaned up.
That reporter's gonna be here.

895
00:55:29,793 --> 00:55:31,954
Why do the interview?
That reporter was wack.

896
00:55:32,128 --> 00:55:35,256
Because it's time we took a stand
and show that we're committed.

897
00:55:35,432 --> 00:55:37,400
All right? We're not arrogant or lazy.

898
00:55:37,567 --> 00:55:39,728
We can do this. Our way.

899
00:55:52,215 --> 00:55:55,582
So why are we doing another article
on the Christmas strike?

900
00:55:55,752 --> 00:55:57,652
Evenhanded reporting.

901
00:55:57,821 --> 00:56:01,052
That's good then, because l thought
your last article sold us short.

902
00:56:01,224 --> 00:56:05,558
l do believe men are capable of doing
more to help out during the holidays.

903
00:56:05,729 --> 00:56:07,321
And they should.

904
00:56:08,164 --> 00:56:10,155
Who knew
you were so enlightened?

905
00:56:10,333 --> 00:56:11,800
Hey, you know l was wondering...

906
00:56:11,968 --> 00:56:14,596
...do you wanna go to a concert
with me on Christmas Eve?

907
00:56:14,771 --> 00:56:17,433
Was everything you said a ploy
to get me to go on a date?

908
00:56:17,607 --> 00:56:19,006
l figured it couldn't hurt.

909
00:56:19,175 --> 00:56:20,506
l should have known.

910
00:56:20,677 --> 00:56:22,577
Yes, but will you go?

911
00:56:22,946 --> 00:56:24,345
-Right on time.
-Hi.

912
00:56:24,514 --> 00:56:26,448
This is my photographer,
Rick Daniels.

913
00:56:26,616 --> 00:56:29,084
-This is Mr. Robertson.
-Nice to meet you.

914
00:56:29,252 --> 00:56:31,345
You ready to give us
your side of this story?

915
00:56:31,521 --> 00:56:32,852
Yes, l am. Come right in.

916
00:56:33,022 --> 00:56:34,785
Very good.

917
00:56:37,494 --> 00:56:39,792
-That's her.
-God.

918
00:56:40,230 --> 00:56:42,994
l can't remember the last time
l went shopping for fun.

919
00:56:43,166 --> 00:56:46,067
-l mean, even after work.
-Me either.

920
00:56:46,236 --> 00:56:49,296
Oh, look, a new striker for the cause.

921
00:56:49,472 --> 00:56:51,030
-Good.
-Yeah.

922
00:56:52,609 --> 00:56:55,442
l don't think l remember
this many men down here, ever.

923
00:56:55,612 --> 00:56:58,342
Yeah, don't look too close,
they don't look too happy.

924
00:56:58,782 --> 00:57:01,376
Good. Maybe they're starting
to appreciate us more.

925
00:57:01,551 --> 00:57:03,746
Look, that dress is beautiful.

926
00:57:03,920 --> 00:57:05,911
Well, let's get in there, girl.

927
00:57:06,089 --> 00:57:09,286
l was thinking l'd like to buy a dress
for Stephen's faculty party.

928
00:57:09,459 --> 00:57:11,893
Well, you should do it then.

929
00:57:13,863 --> 00:57:17,128
Oh, you said this strike
was gonna light a fire in town.

930
00:57:17,300 --> 00:57:19,996
-Feel the heat, honey.
-On strike. On strike.

931
00:57:45,995 --> 00:57:47,860
Call off the strike?

932
00:57:48,965 --> 00:57:51,593
No. No, l'm afraid not.

933
00:57:55,071 --> 00:57:57,301
Please, Mom.

934
00:57:58,975 --> 00:58:00,408
We need you.

935
00:58:00,577 --> 00:58:02,204
Did you see
the decorations outside?

936
00:58:02,378 --> 00:58:05,006
Jeremy and l forgot how much fun
it was to put them up.

937
00:58:05,181 --> 00:58:07,206
But we really missed you.

938
00:58:07,917 --> 00:58:10,750
Jeremy tried to tell Dad
to put our old ornaments...

939
00:58:10,920 --> 00:58:12,683
...the angel one you love,
on the tree.

940
00:58:16,926 --> 00:58:19,224
lt still looks nice.

941
00:58:19,395 --> 00:58:23,422
Hey, why don't you play me
that song that you're writing?

942
00:58:23,600 --> 00:58:26,433
l'd love to Mom, but l can't.

943
00:58:27,270 --> 00:58:28,532
Why not?

944
00:58:28,705 --> 00:58:31,003
Brittany won't help me
with my Christmas party...

945
00:58:31,174 --> 00:58:33,005
...because she joined your strike.

946
00:58:33,176 --> 00:58:35,406
l gotta go do all the stuff
for the party.

947
00:58:35,578 --> 00:58:37,045
l thought about canceling it...

948
00:58:37,213 --> 00:58:39,545
...but l figure it's one
of the last Christmases...

949
00:58:39,716 --> 00:58:41,684
...all of my friends
will be together.

950
00:58:41,918 --> 00:58:43,909
l've played
with those guys a lot of years.

951
00:58:44,087 --> 00:58:46,715
Well, you'll stay in touch
when you're at Oberlin.

952
00:58:46,890 --> 00:58:50,690
Yeah, but it will never be the same.

953
00:58:53,496 --> 00:58:55,225
l'll see you later, Mom.

954
00:59:39,342 --> 00:59:41,435
Well, hello there.

955
00:59:41,611 --> 00:59:44,580
l didn't expect to see you
back here tonight.

956
00:59:47,517 --> 00:59:49,246
What's wrong?

957
00:59:51,955 --> 00:59:55,982
Mom, l know that you don't agree
with the strike, but....

958
00:59:56,159 --> 00:59:58,992
l never said that.

959
00:59:59,162 --> 01:00:02,928
You're like me. Or l'm like you.
Whatever.

960
01:00:03,099 --> 01:00:05,659
You don't hide your feelings well
and l can tell.

961
01:00:06,402 --> 01:00:11,704
Anyway, l hope you understand
that all the women who are on strike...

962
01:00:12,108 --> 01:00:15,509
...we just want our families
to appreciate how hard we work...

963
01:00:15,945 --> 01:00:18,004
...for everything to be nice
on the holidays.

964
01:00:18,181 --> 01:00:20,547
And sometimes we just need
some help from them.

965
01:00:20,717 --> 01:00:22,344
You can understand that, right?

966
01:00:24,354 --> 01:00:26,948
Yes, l can.

967
01:00:27,724 --> 01:00:31,660
l just want Christmas
to be perfect for the boys...

968
01:00:32,428 --> 01:00:35,158
...like it was for us
when Dad was alive.

969
01:00:35,798 --> 01:00:38,494
lt wasn't perfect then, honey.

970
01:00:38,668 --> 01:00:40,693
Sure it was.

971
01:00:41,337 --> 01:00:43,567
We were always so happy.

972
01:00:43,740 --> 01:00:46,573
l can still hear Dad singing
''Up on the Housetop.''

973
01:00:46,743 --> 01:00:49,075
We were happy...

974
01:00:49,245 --> 01:00:52,009
...because we were always together
at that time of year...

975
01:00:52,181 --> 01:00:55,878
...with family members
and friends around.

976
01:00:56,052 --> 01:00:59,385
But it certainly wasn't perfect.

977
01:00:59,555 --> 01:01:03,286
Don't you remember the year
that l burned the turkey to a crisp?

978
01:01:03,459 --> 01:01:04,858
Actually, l do remember that.

979
01:01:05,028 --> 01:01:08,088
And the year that your father
forgot to get me a present...

980
01:01:08,264 --> 01:01:13,099
...and wrote that silly poem
on a paper towel to apologize?

981
01:01:13,269 --> 01:01:16,136
You loved that poem. l remember
you cried when you read it.

982
01:01:16,572 --> 01:01:19,871
And it hangs in my kitchen
every Christmas.

983
01:01:20,043 --> 01:01:22,637
Your father was definitely unique...

984
01:01:23,913 --> 01:01:25,778
...and l loved him for that.

985
01:01:27,150 --> 01:01:28,777
Always will.

986
01:01:29,686 --> 01:01:34,453
Remember, Joy, the holidays
are not about the trappings.

987
01:01:35,692 --> 01:01:40,994
And families evolve
and change as we get older.

988
01:01:42,699 --> 01:01:45,532
l've never been a big fan of change.

989
01:01:46,302 --> 01:01:50,671
And that has been true
ever since you were a little girl.

990
01:01:55,278 --> 01:02:01,683
Don't most strikes end
when they find a middle ground?

991
01:02:03,286 --> 01:02:05,880
Rosemary told me they settled
the grocery strike..

992
01:02:06,055 --> 01:02:07,682
They did?

993
01:02:08,691 --> 01:02:09,749
How?

994
01:02:09,926 --> 01:02:12,156
Each side gave a little.

995
01:02:14,664 --> 01:02:19,124
Try looking at it
from your family's perspective.

996
01:02:19,302 --> 01:02:25,764
And think about what it is
that you really care about.

997
01:02:30,880 --> 01:02:32,211
l love you, Mom.

998
01:02:32,715 --> 01:02:34,740
l love you too.

999
01:02:35,885 --> 01:02:37,614
And l am proud of you.

1000
01:02:53,803 --> 01:02:56,636
-Hey, good morning.
-Hi.

1001
01:02:58,007 --> 01:02:59,133
What was that for?

1002
01:02:59,308 --> 01:03:03,438
Just thinking about something
my mom said last night.

1003
01:03:03,813 --> 01:03:05,713
What's so interesting
that you're reading?

1004
01:03:05,882 --> 01:03:07,281
Nothing.

1005
01:03:07,450 --> 01:03:08,542
-Wait.
-Where were we?

1006
01:03:08,718 --> 01:03:10,948
-What?
-Hey, what is this?

1007
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:13,281
Why don't you want me
to see it?

1008
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:16,883
ls this what l think it is?

1009
01:03:17,059 --> 01:03:20,290
Well, they wanted
another perspective on the strike.

1010
01:03:20,830 --> 01:03:23,856
See? We didn't do such a bad job
decorating the tree there.

1011
01:03:25,268 --> 01:03:27,828
You ordered gifts
off some impersonal website?

1012
01:03:28,004 --> 01:03:30,666
They guarantee delivery by Christmas.
lt's not impersonal.

1013
01:03:30,840 --> 01:03:33,536
Mark said you fill out a checklist
and the online shopper--

1014
01:03:33,709 --> 01:03:35,574
Ordered a prepackaged
Christmas dinner?

1015
01:03:35,745 --> 01:03:38,236
lt's one of those services they offered.
lt's gourmet.

1016
01:03:38,414 --> 01:03:40,245
We ordered those
candied yams you love.

1017
01:03:40,416 --> 01:03:43,180
l love the ones my mother makes.

1018
01:03:44,520 --> 01:03:46,317
You called me ''Yulezilla''?

1019
01:03:46,489 --> 01:03:48,013
Well, that was actually her idea.

1020
01:03:48,191 --> 01:03:53,026
All l said was that sometimes
you can be a little intense.

1021
01:03:53,196 --> 01:03:54,629
Somebody has to be intense...

1022
01:03:54,797 --> 01:03:56,924
...with all these parties
that you're throwing.

1023
01:03:57,099 --> 01:04:00,034
That you're throwing in my face.
Mark's party, faculty party.

1024
01:04:00,203 --> 01:04:04,299
-We got the cookies for the banquet--
-Honey, honey, look, l get it.

1025
01:04:04,473 --> 01:04:06,703
But you asked us to help,
and now we're helping.

1026
01:04:06,876 --> 01:04:10,334
And it may not be exactly the way
you would do it, but it is nice.

1027
01:04:11,981 --> 01:04:17,009
l mean, maybe you need to think about
what it is you really want.

1028
01:04:36,439 --> 01:04:38,464
Hey, we just got your
Christmas card.

1029
01:04:38,641 --> 01:04:40,871
We need to get the girls together.

1030
01:04:41,043 --> 01:04:43,011
You got our card? Can l see it?

1031
01:04:43,646 --> 01:04:45,671
Sure. lt's over here on my computer.

1032
01:04:47,383 --> 01:04:49,044
On your computer?

1033
01:05:01,697 --> 01:05:02,721
Mark's song.

1034
01:05:17,580 --> 01:05:19,104
lt's kind of fun, huh?

1035
01:05:19,548 --> 01:05:21,482
Can you play that again?

1036
01:05:26,188 --> 01:05:28,850
So why do you wanna get
the girls together?

1037
01:05:33,763 --> 01:05:37,028
Hey, guys. l think this strike
is getting out of hand.

1038
01:05:37,199 --> 01:05:40,430
l could have killed my editor
when l saw that ''Yulezilla'' reference...

1039
01:05:40,603 --> 01:05:42,230
...that he added to my article.

1040
01:05:42,405 --> 01:05:44,498
''Sound bites sell papers,''
he says.

1041
01:05:44,674 --> 01:05:46,266
You know, Stephen never said that.

1042
01:05:46,442 --> 01:05:49,343
lt's chaos at my house,
but that doesn't ruffle my feathers...

1043
01:05:49,512 --> 01:05:51,639
...as long as my husband
gives me respect...

1044
01:05:51,814 --> 01:05:54,078
-...and cooperation in the process.
-Exactly.

1045
01:05:54,250 --> 01:05:56,878
-lsn't that what this strike was about?
-ls it worth it?

1046
01:05:57,053 --> 01:05:59,886
Glen's helping but it seems
all we do is argue anymore.

1047
01:06:00,056 --> 01:06:03,048
l want the strike to succeed,
but l don't wanna ruin Christmas.

1048
01:06:03,225 --> 01:06:05,352
No, no one does. So l was thinking--

1049
01:06:05,528 --> 01:06:09,123
All right ladies, look.
There is a galvanized community...

1050
01:06:09,298 --> 01:06:11,266
...of women who are
depending on us now.

1051
01:06:11,434 --> 01:06:14,164
When the going gets tough,
we have to raise the stakes.

1052
01:06:14,337 --> 01:06:15,861
-What if--?
-l completely agree...

1053
01:06:16,038 --> 01:06:18,233
-...but how do we do that?
-l know how.

1054
01:06:18,407 --> 01:06:21,808
We use a different kind of media
that will reach a wider audience.

1055
01:06:21,978 --> 01:06:24,412
Great idea.
Keep the pressure on.

1056
01:06:24,580 --> 01:06:26,445
-Exactly.
-What type of media?

1057
01:06:26,615 --> 01:06:28,048
Bigger.

1058
01:06:28,784 --> 01:06:31,548
-lnternet.
-Open house. l could cater it.

1059
01:06:31,721 --> 01:06:34,554
And l have a friend
at Channel Eight.

1060
01:06:37,893 --> 01:06:39,986
Mom barely said a word
when she got home.

1061
01:06:41,163 --> 01:06:43,028
She's usually so happy
this time of year.

1062
01:06:43,199 --> 01:06:44,894
lt kind of sucks to see her
this way.

1063
01:06:45,067 --> 01:06:47,433
Well, l'm not feeling
so chipper myself.

1064
01:06:47,603 --> 01:06:50,629
The tree doesn't look so bad.
lt's not how Mom would've done it--

1065
01:06:50,806 --> 01:06:53,969
Mark! Please, enough. l get it.

1066
01:07:00,116 --> 01:07:02,243
l'm gonna go down
to the office and work.

1067
01:07:02,418 --> 01:07:03,942
Okay, Dad.

1068
01:07:07,390 --> 01:07:09,756
Merry Christmas to you too.

1069
01:07:13,662 --> 01:07:15,892
Not the same night.

1070
01:07:25,474 --> 01:07:26,702
Mom, it's official.

1071
01:07:26,876 --> 01:07:28,366
l just got the notice online.

1072
01:07:28,544 --> 01:07:31,513
l'm in early decision, and the coach
is holding a spot for me.

1073
01:07:31,680 --> 01:07:35,343
l'm gonna play D-3 ball at Bowdoin.
This is so freaking awesome.

1074
01:07:35,518 --> 01:07:38,976
-Oh, gosh, honey, l'm so proud of you.
-l can't wait to tell Dad.

1075
01:07:39,155 --> 01:07:42,647
l'm gonna go tell Ryan now. This is
gonna be the best Christmas ever!

1076
01:08:11,420 --> 01:08:16,016
l had a feeling you'd call.
l just heard.

1077
01:08:16,192 --> 01:08:17,887
l'm so happy for him, l really am.

1078
01:08:18,060 --> 01:08:21,496
lt's just that Bowdoin is so far away.

1079
01:08:21,664 --> 01:08:24,292
l was hoping he would get
a scholarship closer.

1080
01:08:24,467 --> 01:08:27,402
With Mark going to Oberlin...

1081
01:08:27,770 --> 01:08:31,934
...l was thinking maybe even
Chapman, so one of them could....

1082
01:08:32,741 --> 01:08:34,868
Oh, baby.

1083
01:08:35,211 --> 01:08:39,875
He said this is gonna be
the best Christmas ever.

1084
01:09:08,811 --> 01:09:11,211
Jeremy's really happy.

1085
01:09:13,716 --> 01:09:15,809
Yeah, he deserves to be.

1086
01:09:15,985 --> 01:09:18,613
Yes, he does.

1087
01:09:19,755 --> 01:09:21,916
But it's sure gonna be empty
around here...

1088
01:09:22,091 --> 01:09:24,457
...when he and Mark leave.

1089
01:09:25,761 --> 01:09:28,195
l just hope between girls
and music...

1090
01:09:28,364 --> 01:09:31,162
...that Mark actually finds time
to make it to college.

1091
01:09:33,135 --> 01:09:35,763
Yeah, our son, the rocker heartthrob.

1092
01:09:35,938 --> 01:09:37,599
Yeah.

1093
01:09:42,511 --> 01:09:46,311
So how are
party preparations going?

1094
01:09:48,617 --> 01:09:51,108
Not bad, actually.

1095
01:09:53,055 --> 01:09:56,252
-Who's cooking? Not you, l hope.
-No. No.

1096
01:10:00,062 --> 01:10:01,620
Yeah, l found a caterer.

1097
01:10:03,699 --> 01:10:05,189
Good.

1098
01:10:06,402 --> 01:10:08,029
Yeah.

1099
01:10:10,306 --> 01:10:11,830
Yeah.

1100
01:10:17,813 --> 01:10:21,146
All right, well, good night.

1101
01:10:26,855 --> 01:10:28,755
Good night.

1102
01:10:35,998 --> 01:10:37,932
All right. Well, just please hurry.

1103
01:10:38,100 --> 01:10:39,761
Thank you.

1104
01:10:41,537 --> 01:10:43,596
Dad, did you see
the e-mail l forwarded you?

1105
01:10:43,772 --> 01:10:44,796
What?

1106
01:10:44,974 --> 01:10:47,067
Gifts have been delayed
until after Christmas.

1107
01:10:47,376 --> 01:10:48,673
What?

1108
01:10:48,844 --> 01:10:50,175
l can't deal with that now.

1109
01:10:50,346 --> 01:10:53,941
The caterers are late. l've gotta get
this wine out. Mark, what is that stuff?

1110
01:10:54,717 --> 01:10:57,481
Wow, Mom. You look amazing.

1111
01:10:57,653 --> 01:10:58,915
Thank you, honey.

1112
01:10:59,088 --> 01:11:01,318
Mark, whatever that is,
put that stuff away.

1113
01:11:01,490 --> 01:11:02,752
The party's about to start.

1114
01:11:05,160 --> 01:11:07,492
l know it is.

1115
01:11:12,601 --> 01:11:15,399
Oh, the galleys for your new book.

1116
01:11:15,571 --> 01:11:19,007
Yeah. l promised the department
they'd get the first copies.

1117
01:11:19,174 --> 01:11:22,041
But after you, of course.

1118
01:11:22,211 --> 01:11:24,179
l'm sure it's wonderful. Always is.

1119
01:11:25,547 --> 01:11:28,880
-Oh, Stephen.
-Oh, there's the caterers.

1120
01:11:32,288 --> 01:11:33,312
-Hi.
-Hi.

1121
01:11:33,489 --> 01:11:35,013
Come in, come in.

1122
01:11:35,190 --> 01:11:36,885
Thank God you're here.

1123
01:11:37,059 --> 01:11:39,220
Oh, it's down the hall on the left.

1124
01:11:39,395 --> 01:11:42,387
You're using these caterers?
They're Sharon's biggest competitor.

1125
01:11:42,564 --> 01:11:44,429
What was l to do?
l had to hire somebody.

1126
01:11:44,600 --> 01:11:45,828
Your chairman's here.

1127
01:11:46,001 --> 01:11:47,764
-Hey, hey, Betty.
-Hi.

1128
01:11:47,936 --> 01:11:50,131
-Welcome. Raymond, good to see you.
-Stephen.

1129
01:11:50,306 --> 01:11:51,364
Come on in.

1130
01:11:51,540 --> 01:11:53,508
Oh, it's so lovely.

1131
01:11:53,676 --> 01:11:56,008
We're still kind of getting set up here,
but....

1132
01:11:56,178 --> 01:11:57,236
Very Christmassy.

1133
01:11:57,413 --> 01:11:58,812
-Hello.
-Hey, Grandma.

1134
01:11:58,981 --> 01:12:00,744
Didn't know you'd be here
for my party.

1135
01:12:00,916 --> 01:12:02,247
You didn't have to dress up.

1136
01:12:02,418 --> 01:12:03,976
Your party?

1137
01:12:04,153 --> 01:12:05,552
l thought that was last night.

1138
01:12:05,721 --> 01:12:07,848
Some guys had a gig,
so we moved it to tonight.

1139
01:12:08,023 --> 01:12:11,015
Mind helping me get ready?
They're going to be here any minute.

1140
01:12:11,660 --> 01:12:16,427
But your dad's faculty party
is right now.

1141
01:12:16,598 --> 01:12:18,156
l need to speak to you.

1142
01:12:18,334 --> 01:12:20,029
There's food right there.

1143
01:12:20,202 --> 01:12:22,033
There's something
that you need to know.

1144
01:12:22,204 --> 01:12:24,434
-What are they doing here?
-Mrs. Johnson.

1145
01:12:25,007 --> 01:12:26,497
-Hi. Hi, dudes.
-Hey.

1146
01:12:27,376 --> 01:12:30,641
-Who are all these people?
-Mark.

1147
01:12:31,480 --> 01:12:34,108
-Hey, what's going on?
-lt's my party, Dad.

1148
01:12:34,450 --> 01:12:35,644
-Tonight?
-Yeah.

1149
01:12:35,818 --> 01:12:38,013
-What's the team doing here?
-You know them all.

1150
01:12:38,187 --> 01:12:40,087
l figured you had all the food....

1151
01:12:40,255 --> 01:12:43,019
You didn't think to ask
if l minded if you crashed my party?

1152
01:12:43,192 --> 01:12:44,921
Cool your jets. lt's not a big deal.

1153
01:12:45,094 --> 01:12:48,461
lt is a big deal. You didn't think
to tell me you're having your party...

1154
01:12:48,630 --> 01:12:50,689
...on the same night
l'm having my party?

1155
01:12:50,866 --> 01:12:54,029
l put it on the calendar on the fridge.
All you had to do was check.

1156
01:12:54,203 --> 01:12:56,865
That fridge is so covered up,
l couldn't find my mother...

1157
01:12:57,039 --> 01:12:59,132
-...if she was pinned on it.
-Funny, Dad.

1158
01:12:59,308 --> 01:13:01,970
-lt's not funny.
-l knew when l first heard about it...

1159
01:13:02,144 --> 01:13:05,272
...this Christmas strike
was going to be trouble.

1160
01:13:05,447 --> 01:13:07,881
Trouble?
ls that what you think this is?

1161
01:13:08,050 --> 01:13:10,245
You're lucky l even came with you
to this party.

1162
01:13:10,586 --> 01:13:12,144
You've had it easy so far...

1163
01:13:12,388 --> 01:13:15,482
...l'm about to drop the strike hammer
on you, Raymond.

1164
01:13:15,657 --> 01:13:16,851
Excuse me.

1165
01:13:17,025 --> 01:13:18,856
But sweetie....

1166
01:13:19,027 --> 01:13:20,051
Excuse me.

1167
01:13:20,229 --> 01:13:22,823
Stephen, sorry,
we'll have to be going.

1168
01:13:22,998 --> 01:13:26,263
Honey, honey, let me handle this.
Raymond, Betty. Betty.

1169
01:13:26,435 --> 01:13:29,461
lt's so nice to have you here, really.
Come on in here, please.

1170
01:13:29,638 --> 01:13:31,435
We're having an issue
with our sons.

1171
01:13:31,607 --> 01:13:34,098
But you know what it's like
with teenage boys, right?

1172
01:13:34,276 --> 01:13:35,743
-Of course.
-Have a nice drink.

1173
01:13:35,911 --> 01:13:37,071
Hello, everyone.

1174
01:13:37,246 --> 01:13:38,611
You know each other.

1175
01:13:39,181 --> 01:13:41,115
Hey, that's not for you.

1176
01:13:41,283 --> 01:13:42,944
Give me that.

1177
01:13:44,553 --> 01:13:46,453
Just hold on one second.

1178
01:13:46,889 --> 01:13:49,949
-Hey, party's in the other room.
-Excuse me for one moment.

1179
01:13:50,459 --> 01:13:53,895
-Mark, in the family room.
-We're going to the family room.

1180
01:13:54,062 --> 01:13:56,257
-l've got this.
-Thanks, Mom.

1181
01:13:57,166 --> 01:13:59,066
Sorry, bro.
head to the family room, okay.

1182
01:13:59,234 --> 01:14:01,293
Meet you in there.
Donald, family room, okay?

1183
01:14:01,470 --> 01:14:02,960
Right through here.

1184
01:14:04,440 --> 01:14:05,839
Hi. Come on in.

1185
01:14:09,611 --> 01:14:11,841
-Plate, plate, plate!
-Okay, okay.

1186
01:14:12,014 --> 01:14:13,743
Mom, we got it. We got this, okay?

1187
01:14:13,916 --> 01:14:16,316
-Let's go, bro. Yeah.
-Okay.

1188
01:14:16,485 --> 01:14:19,511
-Merry Christmas. Right in there.
-Merry Christmas.

1189
01:14:22,791 --> 01:14:25,783
This isn't our party, we're in here.
Come on. Sorry about that.

1190
01:14:28,130 --> 01:14:29,927
Yeah, you know how kids are.

1191
01:14:31,066 --> 01:14:32,829
And the food's in the dining room.

1192
01:14:33,001 --> 01:14:37,165
-Hello.
-Yeah. Thank you so much.

1193
01:14:37,973 --> 01:14:39,372
Okay, you guys have fun...

1194
01:14:39,541 --> 01:14:42,510
...but keep it down to a dull roar,
okay?

1195
01:14:44,580 --> 01:14:46,241
ls that all?

1196
01:14:48,917 --> 01:14:51,351
The galleys of Stephen's new book,
everybody.

1197
01:14:51,520 --> 01:14:53,647
Here you go.

1198
01:14:53,822 --> 01:14:55,380
-Mr. Ziff?
-Thank you.

1199
01:14:55,557 --> 01:14:57,923
-l'm sure you're gonna love it.
-Thank you.

1200
01:14:59,495 --> 01:15:00,621
Hey, baby.

1201
01:15:00,796 --> 01:15:03,424
-You are amazing.
-Love you.

1202
01:15:03,599 --> 01:15:04,896
Oh, look who's here.

1203
01:15:06,034 --> 01:15:07,433
-Hi.
-Hi.

1204
01:15:07,603 --> 01:15:11,198
l'm sorry we're late, but l have
something important to tell you.

1205
01:15:11,373 --> 01:15:12,465
Oh, my God.

1206
01:15:12,641 --> 01:15:15,166
-He used them?
-Sharon, l know, it's okay.

1207
01:15:17,012 --> 01:15:19,537
Sharon, what's the important
thing you have to tell me?

1208
01:15:19,715 --> 01:15:21,012
The TV news truck is here.

1209
01:15:21,183 --> 01:15:22,912
They're setting up to interview you.

1210
01:15:23,085 --> 01:15:26,179
Channel Eight. Like now.

1211
01:15:30,359 --> 01:15:31,883
<i>Strike, strike, strike!</i>

1212
01:15:32,060 --> 01:15:33,687
-There she is.
-Okay.

1213
01:15:36,098 --> 01:15:37,963
Hi, guys.

1214
01:15:38,333 --> 01:15:39,391
This way.

1215
01:15:39,568 --> 01:15:41,763
We're so happy that you came out.
This is great.

1216
01:15:44,540 --> 01:15:45,734
Hi.

1217
01:15:45,908 --> 01:15:49,105
So tell me, Mrs. Robertson,
what does this strike mean to you...

1218
01:15:49,278 --> 01:15:51,542
...and all these women
gathered here?

1219
01:15:53,549 --> 01:15:55,039
Well...

1220
01:15:55,651 --> 01:15:57,278
...l started my Christmas strike...

1221
01:15:57,452 --> 01:16:00,387
...because l wanted my family
to appreciate...

1222
01:16:00,556 --> 01:16:04,151
...all that there is to do around this
house, especially at Christmas time.

1223
01:16:04,326 --> 01:16:07,887
And for them to acknowledge
that l can't do it all myself. l need help.

1224
01:16:08,063 --> 01:16:09,860
And l was amazed to see...

1225
01:16:10,032 --> 01:16:12,967
...how this resonated with
so many women in this community.

1226
01:16:13,702 --> 01:16:16,227
Jeremy,
turn to channel eight real quick.

1227
01:16:16,405 --> 01:16:17,599
Mom's on TV.

1228
01:16:17,773 --> 01:16:20,401
Channel eight. Channel eight.

1229
01:16:21,577 --> 01:16:24,410
<i>And l still believe</i>
<i>in my strike demands...</i>

1230
01:16:24,580 --> 01:16:26,912
<i>...l mean, goals.</i>

1231
01:16:27,082 --> 01:16:28,174
ls that our house?

1232
01:16:28,350 --> 01:16:32,309
<i>l still believe in my strike goals,</i>
<i>they just weren't met.</i>

1233
01:16:32,487 --> 01:16:36,287
<i>My strike goals weren't met</i>
<i>my way.</i>

1234
01:16:36,792 --> 01:16:39,625
<i>l thought Christmas</i>
<i>had to be perfect...</i>

1235
01:16:39,795 --> 01:16:40,887
...especially this year.

1236
01:16:41,063 --> 01:16:44,829
So l put a lot of pressure on myself
and my family in the process.

1237
01:16:45,000 --> 01:16:46,126
Why did you do that?

1238
01:16:46,301 --> 01:16:48,929
Because l was afraid that
with my children growing up...

1239
01:16:49,104 --> 01:16:51,231
...l was becoming obsolete...

1240
01:16:51,406 --> 01:16:55,467
...and l needed to find a way
to slow life down...

1241
01:16:55,644 --> 01:16:57,839
...and to make my family appreciate
what l do...

1242
01:16:58,013 --> 01:16:59,275
...and what we have.

1243
01:16:59,448 --> 01:17:02,884
But what makes Christmas perfect
isn't what we do...

1244
01:17:03,051 --> 01:17:06,282
...it's our love for each other.

1245
01:17:07,456 --> 01:17:11,688
And it should bring us closer
and not split us apart.

1246
01:17:12,594 --> 01:17:14,027
l was hanging on so tightly...

1247
01:17:14,196 --> 01:17:18,292
...and now l realize that
it's really about letting go...

1248
01:17:18,467 --> 01:17:20,901
...and becoming even closer
in the process.

1249
01:17:21,069 --> 01:17:23,196
Letting each other grow
and change.

1250
01:17:25,007 --> 01:17:27,669
But what about the strike?
Where do you go from here?

1251
01:17:30,912 --> 01:17:35,611
Look, l know my family loves me,
and l love them.

1252
01:17:35,784 --> 01:17:37,376
And they've made me understand...

1253
01:17:37,552 --> 01:17:41,579
...that Christmas doesn't have to be
done my way to be wonderful...

1254
01:17:41,757 --> 01:17:45,022
...and it's not about the trappings,
it's about....

1255
01:17:46,194 --> 01:17:50,358
<i>lt's about being together,</i>
<i>real and imperfect.</i>

1256
01:17:51,366 --> 01:17:54,665
<i>And l bet if you asked my guys</i>
<i>right now...</i>

1257
01:17:54,836 --> 01:17:56,997
<i>...they'd agree</i>
<i>that it's really important...</i>

1258
01:17:57,172 --> 01:17:58,867
<i>...to help and support each other.</i>

1259
01:17:59,041 --> 01:18:01,032
<i>At Christmas time</i>
<i>and all year round.</i>

1260
01:18:02,144 --> 01:18:05,739
So really, my strike demands
have been met.

1261
01:18:06,381 --> 01:18:08,542
The message has been heard.

1262
01:18:08,717 --> 01:18:14,713
So l'm here to announce that
my Christmas strike is officially over.

1263
01:18:15,223 --> 01:18:18,454
And l ask everyone else,
on this Christmas Eve...

1264
01:18:18,627 --> 01:18:23,724
...that in the true spirit of Christmas,
you end yours too.

1265
01:18:23,965 --> 01:18:25,694
l guess mine is over too.

1266
01:18:25,867 --> 01:18:27,425
Yeah, she's right.

1267
01:18:28,470 --> 01:18:30,529
Thank you, Mrs. Robertson.

1268
01:18:59,367 --> 01:19:01,597
l work so hard every year.

1269
01:19:01,770 --> 01:19:03,601
Merry Christmas.

1270
01:19:05,006 --> 01:19:07,099
-Merry Christmas.
-l love you.

1271
01:19:07,542 --> 01:19:10,773
l love you so much.

1272
01:19:22,591 --> 01:19:24,354
Merry Christmas.

1273
01:19:24,526 --> 01:19:26,619
Merry Christmas.

1274
01:19:31,233 --> 01:19:34,100
These are delicious.
You must have a very good recipe.

1275
01:19:34,269 --> 01:19:36,134
l do, but it's a secret.

1276
01:19:36,304 --> 01:19:39,603
A close friend just gave me the recipe
and, well, l can't share it.

1277
01:19:41,309 --> 01:19:44,369
You know, it's not exactly
as l would have done it...

1278
01:19:44,546 --> 01:19:47,071
...but l really like it.

1279
01:20:14,876 --> 01:20:16,173
-Mom?
-Mom.

1280
01:20:16,344 --> 01:20:18,107
-Joy?
-Mom. Mom.

1281
01:20:18,280 --> 01:20:19,679
l'm in the family room.

1282
01:20:25,487 --> 01:20:26,920
We have a surprise for you.

1283
01:20:27,088 --> 01:20:28,953
Yeah, l already saw it.

1284
01:20:29,124 --> 01:20:31,388
You guys did a great job. l love it.

1285
01:20:31,560 --> 01:20:35,189
Well, there's more. Jeremy.

1286
01:20:35,697 --> 01:20:38,461
So we all listened
to what you said last night.

1287
01:20:38,633 --> 01:20:40,498
And l just want you to know...

1288
01:20:40,669 --> 01:20:44,264
...that even when l'm at college,
you'll always be my number one...

1289
01:20:46,675 --> 01:20:48,438
-...in here.
-ln here.

1290
01:20:50,545 --> 01:20:53,207
-Love you, Mom.
-Love you too.

1291
01:20:53,982 --> 01:20:58,976
Mom, you do so much for us
and not just at Christmas.

1292
01:20:59,154 --> 01:21:02,681
And we really need to tell you more
and how much we appreciate it.

1293
01:21:02,858 --> 01:21:05,156
So thank you.

1294
01:21:13,835 --> 01:21:16,099
Joy, we know how important
Christmas is to you...

1295
01:21:16,271 --> 01:21:18,296
...because we're so important to you.

1296
01:21:19,407 --> 01:21:21,875
And you mean so much to us.

1297
01:21:22,744 --> 01:21:26,703
You don't have to worry about
this being our last, best Christmas.

1298
01:21:27,382 --> 01:21:32,684
Because we have made
the Robertson family demands...

1299
01:21:32,854 --> 01:21:35,288
...and we have all signed it.

1300
01:21:35,457 --> 01:21:36,651
On a paper towel.

1301
01:21:37,859 --> 01:21:39,986
''The Robertson family
Christmas demands.

1302
01:21:40,161 --> 01:21:45,758
We pledge to be together
and help each other every Christmas...

1303
01:21:46,167 --> 01:21:48,260
...and it doesn't have to be perfect...

1304
01:21:48,436 --> 01:21:52,805
...because being together as a family
is all that really matters.

1305
01:21:53,742 --> 01:21:56,267
Stephen, Mark and Jeremy.''

1306
01:22:01,283 --> 01:22:02,944
Okay.

1307
01:22:11,126 --> 01:22:12,787
Joy.

1308
01:22:24,906 --> 01:22:27,238
Oh, it's my editor.

1309
01:22:27,409 --> 01:22:30,003
Oh, l'm fine, honey. Go get it.

1310
01:22:33,048 --> 01:22:35,141
These turned out beautifully.

1311
01:22:35,317 --> 01:22:38,650
Oh, they did, didn't they?

1312
01:22:38,820 --> 01:22:42,551
l don't know how you got that lnternet
company to deliver all the gifts on time.

1313
01:22:42,724 --> 01:22:44,885
lt was easy.
l had Rosemary call and pretend...

1314
01:22:45,060 --> 01:22:47,585
...that she was doing a story
on consumer complaints...

1315
01:22:47,762 --> 01:22:50,560
...about companies that failed
to live up to their pledges...

1316
01:22:50,732 --> 01:22:52,290
...at the holidays and ruin them.

1317
01:22:53,001 --> 01:22:55,231
Now l know
where l get my militant streak.

1318
01:22:56,171 --> 01:22:57,968
And l actually liked the gifts.

1319
01:22:58,473 --> 01:23:02,500
l actually liked the candied yams,
better than mine.

1320
01:23:02,677 --> 01:23:05,737
l mean, not that l want to do this
every year, but....

1321
01:23:05,914 --> 01:23:08,781
My daughter, the micromanager...

1322
01:23:08,950 --> 01:23:12,442
...would actually consider doing
something another way.

1323
01:23:12,921 --> 01:23:17,449
Well, yes, if it encourages
the participation of the guys, l'm in.

1324
01:23:17,625 --> 01:23:20,856
And besides, l will always
micromanage you at the store.

1325
01:23:21,029 --> 01:23:22,621
Lucky me.

1326
01:23:24,899 --> 01:23:25,923
So, what did he want?

1327
01:23:27,602 --> 01:23:29,069
He said he wants my next book...

1328
01:23:29,237 --> 01:23:33,367
...to be about a modern family
dealing with the stresses of Christmas.

1329
01:23:36,211 --> 01:23:39,271
l think that one's been done already.
What did you say?

1330
01:23:39,447 --> 01:23:40,812
l told him l write fiction.

1331
01:23:42,417 --> 01:23:44,544
-Hey, are we ready?
-All set.

1332
01:23:44,719 --> 01:23:46,949
-ls what ready?
-Oh, you'll find out.

1333
01:23:49,424 --> 01:23:51,153
All right, we'd like to dedicate...

1334
01:23:51,326 --> 01:23:53,453
...this Christmas song
to Joy Robertson.

1335
01:23:53,995 --> 01:23:57,226
Rocking wife, mother, and daughter.

1336
01:23:58,366 --> 01:23:59,856
Hit it.

